d set up light aluminum sun-shields to reduce ambient temperature by sixty to seventy degrees. This provided some relief from the intense heat of Mercury's sunlight while they slept and ate from forward sledges using tubes for nutrition intake.&#10;&#10;These challenges indicate that the explorers faced severe physical and environmental difficulties during their eight-hour drives in the hot desert, primarily due to the extreme temperatures and dry conditions on Mercury.">
