    <edge source=" landing, the labs and quarters for Sanderson’s crew sunk deep into the crust, and the tower that housed the Solar ’scope that Sanderson had built up there ten years before.&#10; &#10; &#10; Twilight Lab wasn’t particularly interested in the Brightside, of course—the Sun was Sanderson’s baby and he’d picked Mercury as the closest chunk of rock to the Sun that could hold his observatory. He’d chosen a good location, too. On Mercury, the Brightside temperature hits 770° F. at perihelion and the Darkside runs pretty constant at -410° F. No permanent installation with a human crew could survive at either extreme. But with Mercury’s wobble, the twilight zone between Brightside and Darkside offers something closer to survival temperatures.&#10; &#10; &#10; Sanderson built the Lab up near the pole, where the zone is about five miles wide, so the temperature only varies 50 to&#10;60 degrees with the libration. The Solar ’scope could take that much change and they’d get good clear observation of the Sun for about seventy out of the eighty-eight days it takes the planet to wheel around.&#10; &#10;" target="The speaker, referred to as the Major, has a strong desire to claim ownership of Mercury by making a perilous journey across the Brightside of Mercury at perihelion, the point in Mercury's orbit when it is closest to the Sun and experiencing extreme heat. He plans to do this by traveling on the surface of the planet using specialized vehicles and equipment, starting from the Twilight Lab near Mercury's northern pole and aiming to reach the opposite twilight zone.&#10;&#10;To accomplish this task, the Major intends to seek help from others, specifically those with the necessary skills and daring attitude required for such a dangerous mission. He brings up McIvers, who is known for being a skilled and daring climber but potentially reckless, as a potential candidate for his team. The Major wants to ensure that his team is well-prepared and able to handle the challenges of Brightside, which may include concerns about how McIvers' daredevil nature could impact the safety and success of the expedition.&#10;&#10;The Twilight Lab, with its extensive knowledge about the Sun and Mercury, will play a crucial role in helping the Major and his team prepare for the journey and increase their chances of success. The lab is located in a twilight zone between Brightside and Darkside, where temperatures are more survivable, making it an ideal starting point for the expedition.">
