red to the scorching heat of the Brightside or the frigid cold of the Darkside.&#10;   &#10;3. The twilight zone near the pole also offers good clear observation of the Sun for about seventy out of Mercury's eighty-eight-day orbit around the Sun, providing ample opportunities for solar observations and research. This location was selected specifically for the Solar 'scope observatory project due to its relatively stable and less extreme temperature conditions compared to other areas on Mercury.">
