    <edge source="1. The group's experiences traveling through a desolate, uninhabitable landscape included moving down into a massive sun-baked gorge with huge cracks on the floor, black cliffs jutting up on either side, and an air filled with a barely visible yellowish mist of sulfur and sulfurous gases. They describe it as a hot, barren hole and no place for any man to go, but the challenge was so powerful you could almost feel it.&#10;2. The significant challenge they faced during their journey was crossing the deep and wide cleft in the broad flat plateau. Although there is a possible crossing point identified as a long, narrow ledge of gray stuff, they need to ensure that the shifting of the ledge has stopped or significantly reduced before attempting to cross. Additionally, they must confirm the stability of the landing area on the other side and be prepared for unexpected changes due to Mercury's unpredictable surface conditions, which include shifting faults, active cones, sulfurous breezes, and treacherous yellow flatlands filled with dust and gases beneath the crust." target="1. The safe route to cross the deep and wide cleft in the broad flat plateau would be the &quot;long, narrow ledge of gray stuff&quot; that the narrator has identified as a possible crossing point. However, before crossing, they need to ensure that the shifting of the ledge has stopped or significantly reduced.&#10;2. It's also essential to consider the stability of the landing area on the other side and determine if it can hold the machines. The narrator mentions learning to read the ground, tell covered faults by the sag of the dust, and spot a passable crack, so these skills will be crucial in determining the safety of the path.&#10;3. Preparedness for unexpected changes is essential due to Mercury's unpredictable surface conditions, which include shifting faults, active cones, sulfurous breezes, and treacherous yellow flatlands filled with dust and gases beneath the crust.&#10;4. Maintaining visual contact with each other at all times will help ensure everyone's safety while crossing the cleft, especially if doing so one or two vehicles at a time to minimize risk.">
