lude shifting faults, active cones, sulfurous breezes, and treacherous yellow flatlands filled with dust and gases beneath the crust.&#10;4. Maintaining visual contact with each other at all times will help ensure everyone's safety while crossing the cleft, especially if doing so one or two vehicles at a time to minimize risk.">
